For {recently-updated} macro it is possible to reverse the currently applied sort (by title, creation, modification). But it doesn't make sense to keep the sort title "recently updated" when a sorted list has been reversed (in order to display pages with oldest modification date). Solution would be

a) change the sort title depending on reverse parameter (false/true/not used) or

b) adding a parameter for the title like

{recently-updated:spaces=global|sort=modified|reverse=true|title=least recently updated}

The {recently-used-labels} macro, however, allows to specify a heading for the table view of this macro.


Thanks in advance!

