I did a site import from another instance, and when viewing the UPM received the following message:
{noformat}
An unexpected error occurred. Please refer to the logs for more information.
{noformat}
So I checked the *server* logs, but there was nothing at all from the UPM.  The javascript console however contained more useful errors:
{noformat}
GET http://localhost:8080/rest/plugins/1.0/notifications/admin 400 (No Host matches server name localhost)
{noformat}
They're still a little misleading, because there is a localhost running on 8080, but it's not running at /, but /confluence.

Fixing the context path fixes the error, but the UPM should not be so thoroughly broken by the context path being incorrect, and surely if the server is uncontactable the error reporting of the UPM should be clearer.

